title: MFK Vyškov
text:
MFK Vyškov is a <a href="Czech%20Republic">Czech</a> <a href="association%20football">football</a> club located in the town of <a href="Vy%C5%A1kov">Vyškov</a> in the <a href="South%20Moravian%20Region">South Moravian Region</a>. It currently plays in the <a href="Czech%20National%20Football%20League">Czech National Football League</a>, the second level of Czech football.
History.
The club changed names on 1 January 2012, changing from SK Rostex Vyškov to MFK Vyškov. Since 2017, the club has been owned by Rainbow World Group who also own Cameroonian side <a href="Rainbow%20FC%20%28Cameroon%29">Rainbow FC</a>.
In the 2020–21 season of the <a href="Moravian-Silesian%20Football%20League">MSFL</a>, which was unfinished because of the <a href="COVID-19%20pandemic">COVID-19 pandemic</a> measures, Vyškov finished first in the incomplete table and was offered participation in the <a href="Czech%20National%20Football%20League">Czech National Football League</a>, which the club accepted.
Czech Cup.
Vyškov has taken part in the <a href="Czech%20Cup">Czech Cup</a> a number of times, reaching the third round in the <a href="2006%E2%80%9307%20Czech%20Cup">2006–07 edition</a>.
